abstract: Google’s billionaire founders, owners of a Boeing 767 that has been the talk of Silicon Valley, are apparently adding another unusually large private jet to their fleet: a Boeing 757.

headline.main: Google Founders Pick Up Another Big Plane

abstract: The rise of open-source cellphone software will challenge wireless handset makers and carriers.
snippet: The rise of open-source cellphone software will challenge wireless handset makers and carriers.
lead_paragraph: There is a lot we don’t know about Google’s cellphone effort, but this much seems clear from the many reports: Google isn’t making a phone, it is developing an open-source cellphone operating system. Google will, no doubt build some proprietary applications that run on it, find manufacturers and cut deals with carriers to deliver a shiny package to consumers.

headline.main: Google, Mozilla and the Open-Source Phone
